Jupyter Notebook of a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) using MobileNetV2. Dataset contains Plastic items and Trash items both having 1933 files. Data was compiled from Kaggle datasets and different images were collected and added to pre-existing dataset. The CNN adapted well to the dataset and gave promising results.

import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.applications import MobileNetV2
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Dense, GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import os
In [ ]:
dataset_dir = '../dataset'
train_dir = os.path.join(dataset_dir, 'train')
val_dir = os.path.join(dataset_dir, 'val')
test_dir = os.path.join(dataset_dir, 'test')

if not os.path.exists(dataset_dir):
    print(f"Error: The dataset directory '{dataset_dir}' was not found.")
    print("Please make sure your folder structure is correct.")
In [ ]:
IMG_SIZE = (224, 224)
BATCH_SIZE = 32
INITIAL_EPOCHS = 20
FINE_TUNE_EPOCHS = 10
LEARNING_RATE = 0.0001
FINE_TUNE_AT = 100
In [ ]:
#Data Loading and Preprocessing 
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=40,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest',
    preprocessing_function=tf.keras.applications.mobilenet_v2.preprocess_input
)

validation_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    preprocessing_function=tf.keras.applications.mobilenet_v2.preprocess_input
)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=IMG_SIZE,
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
    class_mode='binary' 
)

validation_generator = validation_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    val_dir,
    target_size=IMG_SIZE,
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
    class_mode='binary'
)

test_generator = validation_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_dir,
    target_size=IMG_SIZE,
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
    class_mode='binary',
    shuffle=False 
)

print(f"Class indices: {train_generator.class_indices}")

#Model Building 

base_model = MobileNetV2(
    input_shape=IMG_SIZE + (3,),
    include_top=False, # We will add our own classifier
    weights='imagenet'
)

base_model.trainable = False

inputs = Input(shape=IMG_SIZE + (3,))
x = base_model(inputs, training=False)
x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = Dropout(0.2)(x)
outputs = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = Model(inputs, outputs)

#Compiling model
model.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=LEARNING_RATE),
    loss='binary_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

model.summary()

print("\n--- Starting Initial Training ---")
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    epochs=INITIAL_EPOCHS,
    validation_data=validation_generator
)
base_model.trainable = True
for layer in base_model.layers[:FINE_TUNE_AT]:
    layer.trainable = False
model.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=LEARNING_RATE / 10), 
    loss='binary_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

print("\n--- Starting Fine-Tuning ---")
total_epochs = INITIAL_EPOCHS + FINE_TUNE_EPOCHS

history_fine = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    epochs=total_epochs,
    initial_epoch=history.epoch[-1],
    validation_data=validation_generator
)

print("\n--- Evaluating Model on Test Data ---")
loss, accuracy = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy*100:.2f}%")
print(f"Test Loss: {loss:.4f}")

acc = history.history['accuracy'] + history_fine.history['accuracy']
val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy'] + history_fine.history['val_accuracy']

loss = history.history['loss'] + history_fine.history['loss']
val_loss = history.history['val_loss'] + history_fine.history['val_loss']

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(acc, label='Training Accuracy')
plt.plot(val_acc, label='Validation Accuracy')
plt.plot([INITIAL_EPOCHS-1, INITIAL_EPOCHS-1], plt.ylim(), label='Start Fine-Tuning')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.title('Training and Validation Accuracy')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(loss, label='Training Loss')
plt.plot(val_loss, label='Validation Loss')
plt.plot([INITIAL_EPOCHS-1, INITIAL_EPOCHS-1], plt.ylim(), label='Start Fine-Tuning')
plt.legend(loc='upper right')
plt.title('Training and Validation Loss')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Loss')

plt.suptitle('Model Training History', fontsize=16)
plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])
plt.show()

model.save('plastic_classifier.h5')
print("\nModel saved to plastic_classifier.h5")

class_labels = list(test_generator.class_indices.keys())

import tensorflow as tf
import numpy as np
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image
import os
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

MODEL_PATH = '../plastic_classifier.h5'
IMG_SIZE = (224, 224)

CLASS_LABELS = {0: 'Plastic Waste', 1: 'Trash'} #plastic waste-0 and trash-1

def classify_image(model, image_path):
    print(f"\nLoading and Preprocessing Image at path {image_path}")

    try:
        img = image.load_img(image_path, target_size=IMG_SIZE)
        img_array = image.img_to_array(img)
        img_batch = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)
        img_preprocessed = tf.keras.applications.mobilenet_v2.preprocess_input(img_batch)

        print("\nPrediction")
        prediction = model.predict(img_preprocessed)
        score = prediction[0][0]
        if score < 0.5:
            predicted_class_index = 0
            confidence = 1 - score
        else:
            predicted_class_index = 1
            confidence = score

        predicted_class_label = CLASS_LABELS[predicted_class_index]
        print("\nClassification Results")
        print(f"Predicted Class: {predicted_class_label}")
        print(f"Confidence: {confidence:.2%}")
        print("------------------------------")

        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
        plt.imshow(img)
        plt.title(f"Input Image\nPredicted: {predicted_class_label}\nConfidence: {confidence:.2%}")
        plt.axis('off')
        plt.show()


    except FileNotFoundError:
        print(f"\nError: The file was not found at '{image_path}'")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"\nAn error occurred: {e}")
        print("Please ensure it's a valid image file (e.g., JPG, PNG).")


if __name__ == '__main__':
    if not os.path.exists(MODEL_PATH):
        print(f"Error: Model file not found at '{MODEL_PATH}'")
        print("Please ensure your model file is at the specified absolute path.")
    else:
        print(f"--- Loading Model: {MODEL_PATH} ---")
        try:
            loaded_model = tf.keras.models.load_model(MODEL_PATH, compile=False)
            print("Model loaded successfully.")
            user_image_path = input("Enter the path to an image file: ")

            classify_image(loaded_model, user_image_path)

        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Failed to load the model. Error: {e}")

import tensorflow as tf
import numpy as np
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image
import os
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

MODEL_PATH = '../plastic_classifier.h5'
IMG_SIZE = (224, 224)

CLASS_LABELS = {0: 'Plastic Waste', 1: 'Trash'} #plastic waste-0 and trash-1

def classify_image(model, image_path):
    print(f"\nLoading and Preprocessing Image at path {image_path}")

    try:
        img = image.load_img(image_path, target_size=IMG_SIZE)
        img_array = image.img_to_array(img)
        img_batch = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)
        img_preprocessed = tf.keras.applications.mobilenet_v2.preprocess_input(img_batch)

        print("\nPrediction")
        prediction = model.predict(img_preprocessed)
        score = prediction[0][0]
        if score < 0.5:
            predicted_class_index = 0
            confidence = 1 - score
        else:
            predicted_class_index = 1
            confidence = score

        predicted_class_label = CLASS_LABELS[predicted_class_index]
        print("\nClassification Results")
        print(f"Predicted Class: {predicted_class_label}")
        print(f"Confidence: {confidence:.2%}")
        print("------------------------------")

        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
        plt.imshow(img)
        plt.title(f"Input Image\nPredicted: {predicted_class_label}\nConfidence: {confidence:.2%}")
        plt.axis('off')
        plt.show()


    except FileNotFoundError:
        print(f"\nError: The file was not found at '{image_path}'")
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"\nAn error occurred: {e}")
        print("Please ensure it's a valid image file (e.g., JPG, PNG).")
